This paper deals with the problem of solving linear programs under differential privacy, which involves both theoretical and algorithmic aspects. The paper uses techniques from multiplicative weights framework, which is a well-known tool in theoretical computer science. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), which deals with privacy and security issues. The paper also involves the design of efficient algorithms, which suggests that it could belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also deals with machine learning techniques, which suggests that it could belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
